problems with `make extract` (and maybe with xzcat):

for example:

# xzcat /usr/ports/distfiles/kde/kdepimlibs-4.8.3.tar.xz | tar xf -; 
tar: Unable to create kdepimlibs-4.8.3/mailtransport/tests/unittestenv_akonadi/xdgconfig-mysql.fs/akonadi/PaxHeaders.8229/: Is a directory
tar: Unable to create kdepimlibs-4.8.3/mailtransport/tests/unittestenv_akonadi/xdgconfig-mysql.db/akonadi/PaxHeaders.8229/: Is a directory
# echo $?
1

... and `make extract` fails because we use `xzcat` to extract, see bsd.port.mk(5)

gtar works and extract without error and return 0;
# gtar Jxf /usr/ports/distfiles/kde/kdepimlibs-4.8.3.tar.xz
# echo $?
0
